The paper deals with reputation algorithms applied to social networks, specifically Twitter, to identify fake and misleading news. This falls under the category of social networks and information retrieval, which includes sub-categories such as social media analysis (cs.SI), social and information networks (cs.SOC), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) to analyze the titles and descriptions of linked articles, and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) to address the issue of fake news spreading and exerting influence.
